      "post_id" : 4031040,
      "comment_id" : 4379110,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "You should provide a size to the <code>StringBuilder</code> constructor (such as <code>input.length()</code>) to ensure that it won&#39;t need to reallocate. You don&#39;t need to demand a <code>String</code> here; <code>CharSequence</code> suffices. Also, you can separate the allocation of the <code>StringBuilder</code> from the collection of non-digits by writing a separate function that accepts a <code>CharSequence</code> as input and an <code>Appendable</code> instance as an output accumulator."
